The paper focuses on zero-shot learning in computer vision, which is a subfield of computer science that falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of machine learning techniques, specifically convolutional neural networks, to improve zero-shot recognition, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of class attributes and semantic space, which are common topics in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the paper presents experimental results on image datasets, which falls under the category of multimedia (cs.MM).
